<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 KILLED IN 3-CAR CRASH IN LAKESIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two people were killed when their automobile overturned in a three-car accident 
Friday in Lakeside, the California Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred about 2:30 p.m. on California 67 near Johnson Lake Road 
when the driver of one car traveling north stopped abruptly, causing it to 
swerve into the southbound lane, striking a second auto, police said. As the 
second car spun around, it was hit by another northbound vehicle, causing the 
second auto to overturn. 
</P>
<P>
The two victims were the second car's driver and passenger, police said. The 
victims' names had not been released as of late Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
The drivers of the two other cars involved in the accident were uninjured, 
police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
