<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WOUNDED MAN RUNS INTO POLICE STATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A young man with a bullet in his head ran into the lobby of the Pomona Police 
Department Thursday night, telling officers he had been wounded in a drive-by 
shooting. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, identified as Jose Marcos Vargas, was taken by officers to Pomona 
Valley Community Hospital. Officers said late Friday that he was expected to 
recover. 
</P>
<P>
Vargas came running into the station's lobby about 9:30 p.m., announcing to 
officers at the main desk that he had been shot in the head while he was in a 
car traveling on Park Avenue near Grand Street, Lt. Ernie Allsup said. 
</P>
<P>
"There was a bullet in the back of his head and it looked like it followed the 
curve of his scalp," Allsup said. "There's a lump on the top of his head which 
I think is the bullet." 
</P>
