<HEADLINE>
<P>
BONNY TO COACH MARINA GIRLS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pete Bonny has been hired as girls' basketball coach at Marina High School, 
Bonnie Stormont, girls' athletic director, announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Bonny has been the junior varsity coach and a varsity assistant at Newport 
Harbor the past four seasons. He replaces Mike Thorton, who resigned last month 
to become the Orange Coast College women's coach. 
</P>
<P>
Thornton will remain as a teacher at Marina. Bonny, a graduate of Ocean View, 
will serve as a walk-on coach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
