</P>
<P>
CAPISTRANO VALLEY'S JENNIFER SMITH PITCHES NO-HITTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jennifer Smith pitched a no-hitter to lead Capistrano Valley High School to a 
1-0 victory over San Clemente in a South Coast League softball game Friday at 
Capistrano Valley. 
</P>
<P>
It was the second no-hitter this season for Smith, who also has five 
one-hitters. She lost a perfect game on a fifth-inning error. Smith had six 
strikeouts. 
</P>
<P>
Capistrano Valley scored in the seventh on three consecutive singles. With one 
out, Tobi Roquemore, Teresa Doesburg and Alyson Carpenter singled, scoring 
Roquemore with the winning run. 
</P>
<P>
