Saddleback 11, Corona del Mar 2 -- Catcher Kim Carstens and left fielder Amber 
Smith each went three for four with two runs batted and two runs scored to pace 
host Saddleback (21-2, 11-0). The Roadrunners, trailing, 2-1, going into the 
bottom of the fourth, broke the game open with six runs on six hits. Desi 
Abrego, who had no-hit Corona del Mar on Wednesday, pitched the final four 
innings for her 16th victory against two losses. Claudia Rodriguez, 
Saddleback's starting pitcher Friday, had a bases-empty homer. Corona del Mar 
is 2-9 in league play. 
</P>
