<HEADLINE>
<P>
THREE SOFTBALL PLAYERS COMMIT TO FULLERTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three softball players have signed national letters of intent to attend Cal 
State Fullerton in the fall, the school announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Pitcher Kristin Jacobs of Fullerton College, third baseman Charlotte Wiley of 
Contra Costa College, and Japanese pitcher Miho Sasamoto have all committed to 
the school. 
</P>
<P>
Jacobs is 25-7 this season and helped Fullerton to the Orange Empire Conference 
title. Wiley played softball at Contra Costa in 1987 and 1988 and sat out this 
season to improve her grades. 
</P>
<P>
Sasamoto pitcher her high school team to the Japan championship in 1987 and 
1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
