<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
UC IRVINE SLAMS DOOR ON FULLERTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ken Whitworth pitched a six-hitter to lead UC Irvine to a 5-3 victory over Cal 
State Fullerton in a Big West Conference baseball game Friday at Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
Whitworth, a junior right-hander, allowed two runs in the second and one more 
in the fourth. But no Fullerton runner reached second base after the fourth. 
Whitworth retired the final 14 batters he faced. It was the team-leading fifth 
complete game for Whitworth (5-6). Irvine has scored 15 runs in his six losses. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton led, 3-0, after four innings, but Irvine rallied for two runs in the 
fifth and three more in the eighth to take the lead, 5-3. 
</P>
<P>
In the eighth, Ed Luna and Al Rodriguez singled to start the inning for Irvine. 
Chris Gallego singled to score Luna and tie it, 3-3. 
</P>
<P>
Sam Colarusso then replaced Fullerton starter Danny DeVille. Osmar DeChavez 
sacrificed and both runners moved up. Mike Goodcase was intentionally walked to 
load the bases, and Freddie Combs was hit by a pitch to force in a run and give 
Irvine a 4-3 lead. Colarusso threw a wild pitch to bring home Irvine's final 
run. 
</P>
<P>
DeVille took the loss for Fullerton (27-20 overall and 7-6 in conference play). 
Luna had three hits and extended his hitting streak to eight games for Irvine 
(17-29-1, 3-10). 
</P>
<P>
In the California College Athletic Assn: 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Dominguez Hills 2, Chapman 0 -- Rick Davis (7-5) pitched a two-hitter 
with 11 strikeouts for Dominguez Hills (14-25-1, 9-14) at Hart Park in Orange. 
Mike Grahovac had a fifth-inning single, and Jody Garcia had ninth-inning 
single for Chapman. 
</P>
