<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE; 
</P>
<P>
NEW HEAD OF BUILDING ASSOCIATION QUITS TO JOIN HOPKINS DEVELOPMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Michael Flagg, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John Withers, recently named to succeed John Erskine as executive director of 
the Building Industry Assn. of Orange County, is instead resigning from the 
trade association to join a developer. 
</P>
<P>
Withers, director of governmental affairs for 2 years, will head a new 
residential development unit at Hopkins Development Co. in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
The trade association is searching for a new executive director. Erskine, 
director for 7 years, is leaving May 15 to practice law. 
</P>
<P>
The BIA is the lobby for home builders and related businesses. 
</P>
<P>
Hopkins, known primarily as a developer of retail properties, will build both 
houses and condominiums and will concentrate on filling in already developed 
areas rather than building new suburbs, Withers said. 
</P>
<P>
The resignations come during a lull in an ongoing battle between the county's 
powerful real estate industry and slow-growth advocates. 
</P>
<P>
One of the biggest issues likely to face the new executive director is drumming 
up public support for a half-cent sales tax increase to fund construction of 
new roads. That will probably go before the county's voters next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
